==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chaja
<hw>Cha"ja</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Native
name.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The crested screamer of Brazil
(<spn>Palamedea chavaria</spn> <it>syn.</it> <spn>Chauna
chavaria</spn>), so called in imitation of its notes; -- called also
<altname>chauna</altname>, and <altname>faithful kamichi</altname>. It
is often domesticated and is useful in guarding other poultry. See
<er>Kamichi</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chalaza</ent>⟦br⟧
